        <div class="project-title project-pad">
          To Go Games
        </div>
        <div class="project-type project-pad sm-space">
          <h2>Wearable Travel Games</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row j5">
        <div class="col-sm-8 ">
          <h3 class="xs-space">Overview</h3>
          <div class="sm-space">To Go Games was a set of travel friendly games and accessories developed for my senior thesis project. My class‚Äô thesis theme was ‚Äògames‚Äô, and we spent the first semester focused on research; conducting user interviews, taking research field trips, and play testing prototypes. My key takeaway was that games are powerful tools for facilitating interpersonal engagement.<br /><br />
For my final project, I wanted to focus on games as objects of social connection, and noticed that a lot of ‚Äútravel‚Äù games were simply big games scaled down. I saw an opportunity to creating portable games that were designed for travel. The research, designs, and model making were conducting in 2012, but I redesigned the branding document, updated the packaging and took new photography in 2020.</div>

        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4 summary">
          <div>
            <h5>YEAR</h5>
            <h6>2012</h6>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h5>DURATION</h5>
            <h6>3.5 months</h6>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h5>TOOLS</h5>
            <h6>Adobe Illustrator</h6>
            <h6>Solidworks</h6>
            <h6>Fusion 360</h6>
            <h6>3D Printing</h6>
            <h6>Laser Cutter</h6>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
